       Welcome to the Southern Plains Range Research Station Web Site.

                USDA Logo            ARS Logo      SPRRS Logo

   The Southern Plains Range Research Station (SPRRS) is a research
   laboratory administered by the Agricultural Research Service of the
   U.S. Department of Agriculture.  Please select from the choices above
   or below for more information.

   [expbul1a.gif] Table of Contents - Birds eye view of the entire site.
   [expbul1a.gif] Service Region - Interactive map of our region and
                  descriptions of land uses and range types.
   [expbul1a.gif] General Staff - Picture of our staff
   [expbul1a.gif] Scientific Staff  - Brief description of research
                  interests of our scientists.

   [expbul1a.gif] Facilities - Pictures and descriptions of our
                  facilities.
   [expbul1a.gif] Program Areas of the Southern Plains Range Research
                  Station
   [expbul1a.gif] History of the SPRRS - History and photographs of the
                  SPRRS
   [expbul1a.gif] Detailed Information - Practical "how to" guides and
                  technical information from our research.
   [expbul1a.gif] Related World Wide Web Resources - Links to other
                  Internet sites.

